title: The Collected Milk and Cheese (Dark Horse) (1988->)
description:
" A carton of hate. A wedge of spite. A comic book of idiotic genius. " 

    - Ad copy

 
 " [...] follows an anthropomorphic, misanthropic carton of milk and a wedge of 
   cheese. The eponymous 'dairy products gone bad' tend to drink copious quantities 
   of gin and become embroiled in gratuitously violent situations. " 

    - 'pedia entry ( <a href=" http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Milk_and_cheese" rel="nofollow" target="_NEW"> http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Milk_and_cheese</a>  )


---


Contains:

OMNIBUS - "Deluxe hardcover collecting [very nearly] every single stupid Milk and Cheese comic ever made from 1989 to 2010, along with a shit-ton of supplemental awesomeness" ( <a href=" http://evandorkin.livejournal.com/254128.html" rel="nofollow" target="_NEW"> http://evandorkin.livejournal.com/254128.html</a>  ). Digital Lo-Res.

SHORTS - Two additional short stories, published in 2012 in issues ten and eleven of the "Dark Horse Presents" anthology, alongside other non-"Milk and Cheese"-related  material from Dorkin. Traditional scans at higher resolution from Minutemen and DCP.
